HEADWORD: Trireme
<hw>Tri"reme</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>triremis</ets>; <ets>tri-</ets> (see <er>Tri-</er>) +
<ets>remus</ets> an oar, akin to E. <ets>row</ets>. See Row to propel
with an oar.]</ety> <fld>(Class. Antiq.)</fld> <def>An ancient galley or
vessel with tree banks, or tiers, of oars.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trirhomboidal</ent>⟦br⟧
